1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 19=

3
00:01:15,858 --> 00:01:19,218
The fatal injury
is a sharp-force puncture to the skull.

4
00:01:19,938 --> 00:01:21,619
The shape and spacing match the features

5
00:01:21,619 --> 00:01:22,979
of a push dagger.

6
00:01:23,578 --> 00:01:25,938
Judging from the wound angle,

7
00:01:26,218 --> 00:01:29,739
the killer had a height advantage
over the victim during the attack.

8
00:01:30,539 --> 00:01:33,459
Numerous punctate marks
were found on the top of the head,

9
00:01:33,459 --> 00:01:34,739
suspected to be multiple strikes

10
00:01:34,739 --> 00:01:35,858
due to insufficient force.

11
00:01:35,858 --> 00:01:38,059
If the victim is Ding Youcai,

12
00:01:38,259 --> 00:01:39,778
could it be a carjacking?

13
00:01:40,259 --> 00:01:44,339
No cash, phone, or similar items
were found among the pile of clothes.

14
00:01:45,259 --> 00:01:48,378
So the suspect was likely a passenger
who hailed the taxi.

15
00:01:48,699 --> 00:01:50,539
He killed the driver, robbed him,

16
00:01:50,858 --> 00:01:52,378
stole the car, and buried the body.

17
00:01:53,059 --> 00:01:54,776
Ding Youcai's car
belonged to the company.

18
00:01:55,059 --> 00:01:56,979
He returned it after quitting.

19
00:02:02,104 --> 00:02:03,459
Wang Tong, Liu Yang.

20
00:02:04,099 --> 00:02:07,179
Talk to Ding Youcai's former colleagues.

21
00:02:08,778 --> 00:02:11,378
Ye, let's visit his hukou location.

22
00:02:11,818 --> 00:02:13,179
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir. Let's go.

23
00:02:40,899 --> 00:02:41,818
Anything wrong,

24
00:02:41,978 --> 00:02:42,619
Master?

25
00:02:43,258 --> 00:02:44,899
You said your friend

26
00:02:44,899 --> 00:02:49,258
could get the new
AD medication from abroad.

27
00:02:51,619 --> 00:02:53,258
Give me your father's medical records.

28
00:02:55,778 --> 00:02:57,938
Forget it if it's too troublesome.

29
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:03,258
It is troublesome.

30
00:03:09,658 --> 00:03:10,938
Bring me the records.

31
00:03:11,938 --> 00:03:12,658
Okay.

32
00:03:14,179 --> 00:03:15,098
Thanks.

33
00:03:19,258 --> 00:03:21,778
He's definitely Baldy Ding.

34
00:03:22,938 --> 00:03:23,739
No doubt about it.

35
00:03:26,258 --> 00:03:27,098
Ding Youcai.

36
00:03:28,459 --> 00:03:29,658
Baldy Ding is his nickname.

37
00:03:30,258 --> 00:03:32,459
He already had little hair
when he was young.

38
00:03:33,258 --> 00:03:35,059
What happened to him?

39
00:03:36,899 --> 00:03:40,299
We haven't heard from him
in the village for years.

40
00:03:41,459 --> 00:03:45,658
Could you please
tell us about him in detail?

41
00:03:45,978 --> 00:03:46,698
Okay.

42
00:03:48,778 --> 00:03:49,859
Ding Youcai...

43
00:03:50,378 --> 00:03:51,859
Let me get you some water.

44
00:03:53,098 --> 00:03:55,258
He used to be idle and lazy,

45
00:03:55,658 --> 00:03:57,739
and spent all day gambling.

46
00:03:58,059 --> 00:04:01,978
Our village was demolished
a long time ago.

47
00:04:02,258 --> 00:04:04,339
His family had two small houses,

48
00:04:04,859 --> 00:04:06,579
but he squandered and lost them both.

49
00:04:07,658 --> 00:04:10,378
His parents had only him, this one son.

50
00:04:10,378 --> 00:04:13,459
They sold everything they had
to get him a wife.

51
00:04:13,978 --> 00:04:15,378
But he remained unmotivated.

52
00:04:19,018 --> 00:04:20,099
He was still going out

53
00:04:20,099 --> 00:04:21,979
to fool around after he got married.

54
00:04:22,258 --> 00:04:24,299
So his wife didn't get along with him.

55
00:04:24,299 --> 00:04:25,979
They fought a lot.

56
00:04:27,099 --> 00:04:27,818
Thanks.

57
00:04:28,818 --> 00:04:30,378
A few times, it got really bad.

58
00:04:31,018 --> 00:04:32,458
Even the local police came.

59
00:04:33,458 --> 00:04:34,539
He beat his wife?

60
00:04:36,018 --> 00:04:37,979
No, the other way around.

61
00:04:38,458 --> 00:04:41,138
Ding Youcai's wife was fierce,

62
00:04:41,378 --> 00:04:42,859
tall, and strong,

63
00:04:43,299 --> 00:04:44,099
very intimidating.

64
00:04:44,419 --> 00:04:47,059
Ding Youcai usually
got the worst end of their fights.

65
00:04:47,859 --> 00:04:51,659
I'd say they're a perfect match.

66
00:04:52,979 --> 00:04:55,338
But eventually, things calmed down.

67
00:04:56,299 --> 00:04:57,179
Well,

68
00:04:58,219 --> 00:05:00,378
apart from that,
his wife was quite decent.

69
00:05:01,859 --> 00:05:04,219
She gave birth to their son

70
00:05:04,739 --> 00:05:06,779
and took care of her in-laws
until they passed.

71
00:05:08,179 --> 00:05:10,258
Ding Youcai had a son?

72
00:05:11,219 --> 00:05:11,859
Yeah.

73
00:05:12,859 --> 00:05:14,539
What's his name again?

74
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:21,258
Weren't Ding Youcai's wife and son
on the same hukou registration as him?

75
00:05:22,659 --> 00:05:25,179
Ding Youcai's wife
came from the neighboring town.

76
00:05:25,698 --> 00:05:27,659
Her surname was Yu, I think.

77
00:05:29,179 --> 00:05:30,938
She had an urban hukou,

78
00:05:31,378 --> 00:05:33,859
so the child was registered under her

79
00:05:35,258 --> 00:05:39,378
to attend a better school in the county.

80
00:05:40,258 --> 00:05:42,258
Now, it's called the "district."

81
00:05:43,059 --> 00:05:45,219
This was good for the child,

82
00:05:45,859 --> 00:05:48,539
but Ding Youcai wasn't happy about it.

83
00:05:49,059 --> 00:05:52,419
He felt it made him lose face,
having the child register

84
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:53,419
under the mother.

85
00:05:53,898 --> 00:05:56,338
He made a fuss about it several times.

86
00:05:58,059 --> 00:06:00,458
But he couldn't convince his wife,

87
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,258
so he got angry and left to find work.

88
00:06:03,099 --> 00:06:05,138
When did that happen?

89
00:06:08,619 --> 00:06:09,979
Must be about twenty years ago.

90
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:14,818
His son, Ding Yu, is the same age
as my youngest daughter.

91
00:06:14,818 --> 00:06:15,659
They're 25 now.

92
00:06:16,498 --> 00:06:17,539
Where did he go to work?

93
00:06:17,979 --> 00:06:19,059
I have no idea.

94
00:06:20,059 --> 00:06:22,338
Did Ding Youcai
ever come back to the village?

95
00:06:22,779 --> 00:06:25,099
Yes, he came back often.

96
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:27,099
He wouldn't do hard labor

97
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,138
and complained about everything.

98
00:06:29,299 --> 00:06:31,578
H-He couldn't
hold down any job for long.

99
00:06:33,578 --> 00:06:36,138
His wife felt she couldn't rely on him,

100
00:06:36,338 --> 00:06:38,739
so she went to the city and found a job.

101
00:06:39,219 --> 00:06:41,578
Then she took the child
to the city with her.

102
00:06:42,419 --> 00:06:45,578
Can we still get in touch
with Ding Youcai's wife?

103
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:48,099
I'm not that capable.

104
00:06:48,099 --> 00:06:49,458
She was cremated to ashes.

105
00:06:51,659 --> 00:06:54,258
Ding Youcai's wife died of cancer.

106
00:06:55,779 --> 00:06:59,018
Ding Yu was in middle school that year.

107
00:06:59,458 --> 00:07:00,539
That's about 13 years ago.

108
00:07:02,539 --> 00:07:07,659
What is this Ding Yu doing now?

109
00:07:09,018 --> 00:07:10,539
I really have no idea.

110
00:07:11,179 --> 00:07:14,539
Some say Ding Youcai took him away.

111
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:20,299
Others say he just gave him some money
and abandoned him.

112
00:07:22,539 --> 00:07:24,338
But I did see him once later.

113
00:07:31,299 --> 00:07:33,138
- Nice.
- Nice.

114
00:07:38,258 --> 00:07:40,739
- Nice.
- Nice.

115
00:07:41,938 --> 00:07:43,338
Thank you.

116
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:43,938
Thank you.

117
00:07:43,938 --> 00:07:45,779
Come on, thanks, guys.

118
00:07:45,938 --> 00:07:46,498
Come on.

119
00:07:46,659 --> 00:07:48,338
Enjoy the food and drinks.

120
00:07:48,338 --> 00:07:49,779
Enjoy the food and drinks.

121
00:07:50,099 --> 00:07:50,739
Enjoy.

122
00:07:50,739 --> 00:07:51,859
Make yourselves at home.

123
00:07:51,859 --> 00:07:52,818
Alright.

124
00:07:56,659 --> 00:07:57,458
Sit.

125
00:07:57,539 --> 00:07:59,258
Enjoy the food and drinks.

126
00:08:00,338 --> 00:08:03,619
So Ding Youcai got remarried?

127
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:09,458
About nine or ten years ago.

128
00:08:09,938 --> 00:08:14,539
He brought a woman back to the village
and held a wedding banquet.

129
00:08:15,338 --> 00:08:17,979
He didn't ask me
to issue a marriage statement.

130
00:08:17,979 --> 00:08:19,818
I don't know if they got registered.

131
00:08:20,698 --> 00:08:21,818
Then what?

132
00:08:21,818 --> 00:08:25,539
Then he took Ding Yu away.

133
00:08:26,099 --> 00:08:28,179
Ding Yu wasn't good at studying.

134
00:08:28,179 --> 00:08:29,378
He never got into high school.

135
00:08:29,739 --> 00:08:32,899
He probably went to earn money
with his father.

136
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:37,738
What happened to the woman
Ding Youcai brought back

137
00:08:37,738 --> 00:08:39,179
for the wedding banquet?

138
00:08:40,578 --> 00:08:43,899
Well, that woman looked quite young.

139
00:08:45,539 --> 00:08:46,738
She rarely spoke.

140
00:08:47,259 --> 00:08:50,618
She didn't seem much older than Ding Yu.

141
00:08:55,259 --> 00:08:58,098
We might've heard her name back then...

142
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:00,738
But it's been too long.

143
00:09:00,738 --> 00:09:02,419
I-I've forgotten.

144
00:09:06,299 --> 00:09:07,139
Thank you.

145
00:09:08,499 --> 00:09:09,259
No problem.

146
00:09:09,938 --> 00:09:12,259
We'll visit you again
if anything comes up.

147
00:09:12,738 --> 00:09:13,259
Alright.

148
00:09:13,539 --> 00:09:14,139
Anytime.

149
00:09:14,139 --> 00:09:15,019
See you.

150
00:09:15,259 --> 00:09:15,698
Okay.

151
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:19,179
We'll take this back with us.

152
00:09:19,858 --> 00:09:20,818
Okay.

153
00:09:21,139 --> 00:09:21,978
See you.

154
00:09:22,139 --> 00:09:22,698
Take care.

155
00:09:26,539 --> 00:09:27,338
Go back inside.

156
00:09:28,139 --> 00:09:28,738
Thanks.

157
00:09:29,019 --> 00:09:30,139
Take care, officers.

158
00:09:30,139 --> 00:09:30,659
Okay.

159
00:09:39,499 --> 00:09:39,978
Hello?

160
00:09:40,578 --> 00:09:41,259
Ye Qian.

161
00:09:42,379 --> 00:09:43,419
We found something.

162
00:09:43,899 --> 00:09:44,698
Hold on a second.

163
00:09:48,659 --> 00:09:49,338
Go ahead.

164
00:09:50,259 --> 00:09:53,618
We found traces of burnt tin foil
in the soil sample.

165
00:09:53,858 --> 00:09:55,938
It should be
from the funeral paper ingots.

166
00:09:57,139 --> 00:09:59,818
The killer burned spirit money
for the victim?

167
00:10:01,019 --> 00:10:01,818
Who knows?

168
00:10:02,019 --> 00:10:03,938
Maybe it was out of remorse.

169
00:10:04,858 --> 00:10:05,858
Okay, got it.

170
00:10:06,098 --> 00:10:06,698
Talk later.

171
00:10:10,659 --> 00:10:11,299
Master.

172
00:10:11,659 --> 00:10:13,978
We still have
too little information on Ding Youcai.

173
00:10:14,659 --> 00:10:16,419
I think we should start with Ding Yu.

174
00:10:18,059 --> 00:10:21,659
Ding Yu likely settled in town
with his mother.

175
00:10:22,379 --> 00:10:24,299
I'll check his identity records.

176
00:10:25,698 --> 00:10:29,698
You've completely
ruled out robbery-homicide?

177
00:10:30,899 --> 00:10:32,539
I think the victim knew the killer.

178
00:10:32,938 --> 00:10:34,539
Rural folks value their hometown.

179
00:10:35,139 --> 00:10:36,338
That's why the body

180
00:10:36,338 --> 00:10:39,299
was buried somewhere
near Ding Youcai's hometown.

181
00:10:40,499 --> 00:10:41,698
The burnt spirit money

182
00:10:42,139 --> 00:10:44,379
shows that the killer felt guilty.

183
00:10:45,938 --> 00:10:47,179
And I think that CD

184
00:10:48,338 --> 00:10:50,019
was deliberately placed there.

185
00:10:50,858 --> 00:10:53,338
But I haven't figured out why yet.

186
00:11:15,139 --> 00:11:16,539
Please take your belongings.

187
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:17,618
Okay.

188
00:11:17,618 --> 00:11:18,299
Watch for cars.

189
00:11:49,379 --> 00:11:50,139
Over here.

190
00:11:50,299 --> 00:11:50,738
Baby.

191
00:11:50,738 --> 00:11:51,379
I'm here.

192
00:11:53,499 --> 00:11:54,499
Slow down.

193
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:56,578
Over here.

194
00:11:56,858 --> 00:11:57,659
Xixi.

195
00:11:58,419 --> 00:11:59,379
Come here.

196
00:12:02,379 --> 00:12:03,179
Over here.

197
00:12:11,499 --> 00:12:13,059
What did you learn today?

198
00:12:13,578 --> 00:12:14,738
You can't remember?

199
00:12:15,218 --> 00:12:16,578
Were you absent-minded?

200
00:12:16,899 --> 00:12:17,618
No.

201
00:12:17,618 --> 00:12:18,899
Really?

202
00:12:19,259 --> 00:12:20,059
Really.

203
00:12:20,938 --> 00:12:22,098
See anything you like?

204
00:12:24,499 --> 00:12:25,499
You like balloons?

205
00:12:25,938 --> 00:12:27,019
Put on your armor.

206
00:12:27,139 --> 00:12:27,938
Let's get going.

207
00:12:28,618 --> 00:12:29,539
Keep your legs in.

208
00:12:36,858 --> 00:12:37,419
Sweetie.

209
00:12:37,659 --> 00:12:39,659
Balloons aren't safe in the car.

210
00:12:40,059 --> 00:12:41,938
Dad will tie it here for now.

211
00:12:41,938 --> 00:12:43,539
Play with it when we get home, okay?

212
00:12:52,458 --> 00:12:53,578
Is this fun?

213
00:12:53,899 --> 00:12:54,698
Yes.

214
00:13:02,059 --> 00:13:02,938
Hello, officers.

215
00:13:03,419 --> 00:13:04,338
Fang Qihang, right?

216
00:13:04,338 --> 00:13:05,139
Yes.

217
00:13:05,176 --> 00:13:05,938
(Longxi Travels)

218
00:13:05,938 --> 00:13:06,738
Police.

219
00:13:08,818 --> 00:13:09,738
We have some questions.

220
00:13:12,059 --> 00:13:13,379
Let me see your ID first.

221
00:13:13,738 --> 00:13:14,299
Okay.

222
00:13:23,858 --> 00:13:25,016
You run this travel agency?

223
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:26,098
Yeah.

224
00:13:26,818 --> 00:13:29,499
I have my business license
right there on the wall.

225
00:13:32,059 --> 00:13:34,098
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

226
00:13:34,098 --> 00:13:35,259
I haven't done anything.

227
00:13:35,458 --> 00:13:38,098
Then why'd I hear you
ran a matchmaking agency

228
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:40,899
for cross-border marriages?

229
00:13:41,338 --> 00:13:42,139
Pretty trendy, huh?

230
00:13:42,139 --> 00:13:42,938
No.

231
00:13:43,098 --> 00:13:45,338
I completely stopped

232
00:13:45,338 --> 00:13:49,059
the cross-border marriage service
almost ten years ago.

233
00:13:49,139 --> 00:13:49,779
Really.

234
00:13:50,899 --> 00:13:52,539
Officers, have a seat.

235
00:13:52,938 --> 00:13:53,738
Come on.

236
00:13:55,539 --> 00:13:56,259
Here.

237
00:13:56,938 --> 00:13:57,738
Thanks.

238
00:14:00,419 --> 00:14:02,218
Do you know Ding Youcai?

239
00:14:03,899 --> 00:14:06,858
Y-Yes, I know him.

240
00:14:07,259 --> 00:14:08,059
What's wrong?

241
00:14:08,499 --> 00:14:09,899
What did he do?

242
00:14:11,059 --> 00:14:11,738
Officer.

243
00:14:11,938 --> 00:14:13,179
I don't know anything

244
00:14:13,899 --> 00:14:15,659
about what he has done.

245
00:14:16,019 --> 00:14:18,019
We haven't seen each other for years.

246
00:14:18,019 --> 00:14:19,458
Not even a phone call.

247
00:14:20,738 --> 00:14:23,218
But I heard you two were pretty close.

248
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:28,338
We used to drive taxis together

249
00:14:29,139 --> 00:14:30,818
and spent all day gambling.

250
00:14:31,139 --> 00:14:33,618
And we used to play cards, too.

251
00:14:34,098 --> 00:14:36,059
That's how we got to know each other.

252
00:14:36,618 --> 00:14:40,019
But that was nearly ten years ago.

253
00:14:43,659 --> 00:14:44,818
Fang, not driving today?

254
00:14:44,899 --> 00:14:45,698
I just got back.

255
00:14:45,698 --> 00:14:46,218
Alright.

256
00:14:49,499 --> 00:14:50,098
Nine of dots.

257
00:14:50,299 --> 00:14:51,059
I won.

258
00:14:51,338 --> 00:14:52,899
I let you win again? Here, take it.

259
00:14:52,899 --> 00:14:54,218
Seven pairs.

260
00:14:54,218 --> 00:14:55,499
Come on.

261
00:14:55,858 --> 00:14:56,539
Come on.

262
00:14:57,059 --> 00:14:57,738
Ding.

263
00:14:57,738 --> 00:14:58,419
Come on.

264
00:14:58,419 --> 00:14:59,818
Lucky streak today, huh?

265
00:15:00,218 --> 00:15:02,299
Today I'm going to win big time.

266
00:15:02,539 --> 00:15:03,738
I'm winning you today.

267
00:15:05,379 --> 00:15:06,818
I've seen it too many times.

268
00:15:07,379 --> 00:15:09,139
Changing players
is like changing blades.

269
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:12,299
I haven't won money off you in a while.

270
00:15:13,499 --> 00:15:16,019
Well, that depends on your luck.

271
00:15:16,338 --> 00:15:17,259
I'm going to win.

272
00:15:18,539 --> 00:15:19,698
Not working today?

273
00:15:20,098 --> 00:15:21,499
Too few customers in this heat.

274
00:15:21,818 --> 00:15:23,259
We finally got a game together.

275
00:15:23,259 --> 00:15:25,098
I've got to play to satisfy the itch.

276
00:15:25,098 --> 00:15:25,899
Yeah.

277
00:15:27,139 --> 00:15:28,738
Here, watch this.

278
00:15:30,818 --> 00:15:32,139
Did he have any enemies?

279
00:15:36,059 --> 00:15:37,218
Ding Youcai

280
00:15:37,618 --> 00:15:39,419
was a pretty decent guy,

281
00:15:39,419 --> 00:15:41,858
generous and loyal to friends.

282
00:15:42,779 --> 00:15:44,139
As far as I know,

283
00:15:44,458 --> 00:15:46,259
he got along well with everyone.

284
00:15:47,338 --> 00:15:50,938
I wouldn't say he made enemies.

285
00:15:51,259 --> 00:15:53,379
Did he love music

286
00:15:53,938 --> 00:15:54,659
or singing?

287
00:15:57,098 --> 00:15:59,299
He loved listening to Teresa Teng.

288
00:15:59,299 --> 00:16:00,818
He'd hum her tunes all the time.

289
00:16:02,098 --> 00:16:02,818
Red Dragon.

290
00:16:04,578 --> 00:16:05,338
North Wind.

291
00:16:06,379 --> 00:16:07,458
Alright.

292
00:16:08,858 --> 00:16:09,858
So lucky.

293
00:16:11,059 --> 00:16:11,858
How about that?

294
00:16:11,858 --> 00:16:12,698
Pay up.

295
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:13,779
Here.

296
00:16:13,779 --> 00:16:15,019
Unbelievable luck.

297
00:16:15,419 --> 00:16:17,059
You always beat me when you come.

298
00:16:18,499 --> 00:16:19,338
Watch me.

299
00:16:21,059 --> 00:16:21,848
What are you doing?

300
00:16:23,059 --> 00:16:25,019
The battle song sounds,
and money goes around.

301
00:16:34,098 --> 00:16:34,738
Come on.

302
00:16:35,338 --> 00:16:37,098
Watch me clean house today.

303
00:16:39,139 --> 00:16:41,098
You know Ding Youcai had a son?

304
00:16:42,059 --> 00:16:43,059
Yeah.

305
00:16:43,059 --> 00:16:44,179
I've seen him a few times.

306
00:16:44,659 --> 00:16:47,059
The two of them
took shifts driving the taxi.

307
00:16:49,259 --> 00:16:51,338
Ding Youcai made his son drive the taxi?

308
00:16:52,019 --> 00:16:53,659
A minor driving without a license?

309
00:16:53,659 --> 00:16:57,218
Well, Ding Youcai's son
looked older than he was.

310
00:16:57,458 --> 00:16:58,539
As long as he didn't speak,

311
00:16:58,818 --> 00:17:01,499
he could easily pass for someone
in his early twenties.

312
00:17:02,539 --> 00:17:04,818
Besides, driving isn't that hard.

313
00:17:04,939 --> 00:17:06,338
It's all about practice.

314
00:17:06,539 --> 00:17:09,138
A few more runs,
and he got the hang of it.

315
00:17:10,418 --> 00:17:11,499
Straighten the wheel.

316
00:17:11,779 --> 00:17:12,418
Like this.

317
00:17:12,418 --> 00:17:13,658
Now shift into drive.

318
00:17:14,499 --> 00:17:15,299
Yes, okay.

319
00:17:15,299 --> 00:17:16,739
Come on, forward.

320
00:17:17,658 --> 00:17:19,219
This way, come out.

321
00:17:19,219 --> 00:17:20,658
Reverse. Turn the wheel.

322
00:17:20,898 --> 00:17:21,539
Okay.

323
00:17:21,539 --> 00:17:22,898
Back up.

324
00:17:23,259 --> 00:17:24,059
Okay, slow down.

325
00:17:24,059 --> 00:17:26,499
Back up, yeah.

326
00:17:27,019 --> 00:17:28,059
Turn the wheel.

327
00:17:28,059 --> 00:17:29,338
Yes, back up.

328
00:17:29,338 --> 00:17:29,979
Keep going.

329
00:17:30,299 --> 00:17:31,098
Keep going.

330
00:17:32,858 --> 00:17:34,098
Were they close?

331
00:17:36,299 --> 00:17:39,378
Well, he was a teenager.

332
00:17:40,098 --> 00:17:42,779
They argued sometimes.

333
00:17:43,138 --> 00:17:46,418
But the kid was quite sensible to me.

334
00:17:46,939 --> 00:17:48,378
He took shifts for his dad

335
00:17:48,739 --> 00:17:52,418
and seemed to have
several part-time jobs.

336
00:17:53,818 --> 00:17:56,019
Ding Youcai had a girlfriend back then.

337
00:17:56,338 --> 00:17:57,618
Did you know her?

338
00:17:59,618 --> 00:18:02,059
Actually, I introduced her to him.

339
00:18:02,499 --> 00:18:05,019
I was trying to switch careers.

340
00:18:05,338 --> 00:18:06,818
Driving a taxi was too tough

341
00:18:06,818 --> 00:18:08,138
and didn't pay well.

342
00:18:08,299 --> 00:18:10,338
A friend had connections in this field,

343
00:18:10,338 --> 00:18:13,739
so we partnered
and opened that matchmaking agency.

344
00:18:13,858 --> 00:18:15,939
We made some money,
and it was good karma too.

345
00:18:16,338 --> 00:18:18,818
I heard she was a foreign girl?

346
00:18:20,059 --> 00:18:20,779
Look.

347
00:18:20,939 --> 00:18:25,059
It was hard for a single dad
to raise a teenage son.

348
00:18:25,658 --> 00:18:31,059
A man needs a wife
to look after him, right?

349
00:18:31,059 --> 00:18:34,499
I tried finding him a local match first.

350
00:18:34,618 --> 00:18:36,219
But he wouldn't settle

351
00:18:37,019 --> 00:18:38,618
for someone "not good enough",

352
00:18:38,858 --> 00:18:39,858
and the "good ones"

353
00:18:40,539 --> 00:18:42,059
wouldn't look at him twice.

354
00:18:42,338 --> 00:18:44,779
Plus, he insisted on someone
quiet and obedient,

355
00:18:44,779 --> 00:18:46,979
nothing like his former wife.

356
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,779
Since I was doing
the cross-border service,

357
00:18:49,818 --> 00:18:52,019
I found someone for him from abroad.

358
00:18:53,539 --> 00:18:54,898
O-Officers,

359
00:18:55,138 --> 00:18:57,219
I have some business to attend to later.

360
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:58,418
I have an appointment.

361
00:18:58,578 --> 00:19:00,578
Can we continue this another day?

362
00:19:11,699 --> 00:19:13,739
What's wrong? Uncomfortable in this car?

363
00:19:15,418 --> 00:19:16,459
Not at all.

364
00:19:16,939 --> 00:19:18,539
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

365
00:19:18,898 --> 00:19:22,138
It's just my first time in a police car.

366
00:19:22,138 --> 00:19:25,059
I-I'm a bit excited.

367
00:19:26,098 --> 00:19:27,418
You're too kind,

368
00:19:27,418 --> 00:19:30,338
giving me a ride and all.

369
00:19:31,658 --> 00:19:33,258
Back to Ding Youcai's second wife.

370
00:19:34,539 --> 00:19:35,939
Did she marry him willingly?

371
00:19:36,578 --> 00:19:38,019
You followed the legal procedures?

372
00:19:39,138 --> 00:19:40,739
Of course, she did.

373
00:19:41,178 --> 00:19:44,939
I even took him across the border
to meet her family.

374
00:19:45,178 --> 00:19:48,939
He handed the bride price
directly to her parents.

375
00:19:49,539 --> 00:19:52,618
Everything was done by the book.

376
00:19:53,459 --> 00:19:54,739
You charged a hefty fee?

377
00:19:55,578 --> 00:19:57,178
Just the cost price.

378
00:19:57,178 --> 00:20:00,739
A friend's discount, 100,000 RMB.

379
00:20:02,019 --> 00:20:04,699
Tell me about the girl.

380
00:20:04,699 --> 00:20:05,618
In detail.

381
00:20:07,338 --> 00:20:11,338
I need to check my records for that.

382
00:20:11,338 --> 00:20:12,939
It's been a long time.

383
00:20:14,138 --> 00:20:15,699
I just remember

384
00:20:15,858 --> 00:20:19,578
they gave her a Chinese name
when she arrived,

385
00:20:19,578 --> 00:20:21,539
called Yu Meigui.

386
00:20:21,539 --> 00:20:22,979
That's right.

387
00:20:22,979 --> 00:20:26,178
Same surname as his late wife, I think.

388
00:20:26,658 --> 00:20:29,818
The girl was 17 then.

389
00:20:30,699 --> 00:20:31,338
Come on.

390
00:20:31,539 --> 00:20:32,939
Don't give me that look.

391
00:20:33,138 --> 00:20:36,138
That's considered late to marry
and have children where she's from.

392
00:20:37,618 --> 00:20:38,898
But not here.

393
00:20:38,898 --> 00:20:41,338
They had to wait a few years
to register the marriage.

394
00:20:45,618 --> 00:20:48,138
Later, I stopped driving

395
00:20:49,219 --> 00:20:50,658
and got busy with the business.

396
00:20:51,019 --> 00:20:54,418
So I met with Ding Youcai less often.

397
00:20:54,658 --> 00:20:58,259
Eventually, we lost contact completely.

398
00:20:59,779 --> 00:21:00,578
Officers,

399
00:21:01,219 --> 00:21:02,898
what happened to Ding Youcai?

400
00:21:03,259 --> 00:21:07,219
It doesn't sound like he got in trouble.

401
00:21:07,259 --> 00:21:08,898
More like something happened to him.

402
00:21:11,739 --> 00:21:13,098
A set of remains was found.

403
00:21:14,098 --> 00:21:15,378
We suspect it's Ding Youcai.

404
00:21:15,739 --> 00:21:17,098
R-Remains?

405
00:21:19,138 --> 00:21:21,259
If it's confirmed to be Ding Youcai,

406
00:21:22,939 --> 00:21:24,658
then he died three years ago.

407
00:21:29,939 --> 00:21:31,898
But I saw his son just last year.

408
00:21:32,539 --> 00:21:33,858
It was quite a coincidence.

409
00:21:34,219 --> 00:21:35,459
My car broke down that day.

410
00:21:36,098 --> 00:21:37,858
I called a ride-hailing car.

411
00:21:38,138 --> 00:21:40,418
That driver turned out to be his son.

412
00:21:44,578 --> 00:21:45,499
Last four digits.

413
00:21:46,259 --> 00:21:47,059
7482.

414
00:21:49,259 --> 00:21:51,338
Aren't you Ding Youcai's son?

415
00:21:53,858 --> 00:21:56,459
How is your dad doing?

416
00:21:58,459 --> 00:21:59,658
He went back to his hometown.

417
00:22:34,459 --> 00:22:36,858
Harder. Don't act like
you haven't eaten.

418
00:22:37,459 --> 00:22:38,539
I brought some food.

419
00:22:41,618 --> 00:22:42,858
I was thinking,

420
00:22:43,418 --> 00:22:45,378
given the victim's height,

421
00:22:45,378 --> 00:22:46,219
it's quite difficult

422
00:22:46,219 --> 00:22:50,019
to cause such a wound
even if he was sitting down.

423
00:22:51,658 --> 00:22:53,259
What if it's a car seat?

424
00:22:54,378 --> 00:22:57,378
Haven't we already ruled out
the possibility of carjacking murder?

425
00:22:57,578 --> 00:22:59,459
We got a message from the taxi company.

426
00:22:59,658 --> 00:23:01,338
They checked the records.

427
00:23:02,939 --> 00:23:06,178
Ding Youcai didn't
return the car or resign in person.

428
00:23:06,818 --> 00:23:08,259
His son, Ding Yu, did it for him.

429
00:23:08,939 --> 00:23:10,779
Ding Yu had his father's ID card.

430
00:23:11,096 --> 00:23:12,378
He said Ding Youcai had business

431
00:23:12,378 --> 00:23:13,539
and was back in his hometown

432
00:23:13,779 --> 00:23:14,939
and asked him to handle it.

433
00:23:15,939 --> 00:23:17,779
That makes Ding Yu highly suspicious.

434
00:23:19,658 --> 00:23:22,578
Based on the injury
to the victim's skull,

435
00:23:22,968 --> 00:23:24,059
if it happened in the car,

436
00:23:24,059 --> 00:23:26,338
then he was sitting
in the passenger seat

437
00:23:26,338 --> 00:23:29,059
or the right side of the back seat.

438
00:23:29,539 --> 00:23:30,618
Can Ding Yu drive?

439
00:23:31,059 --> 00:23:31,739
Yes.

440
00:23:32,059 --> 00:23:34,818
He started driving taxis
in shifts with his father as a teenager.

441
00:23:37,138 --> 00:23:39,019
Where was Ding Youcai's car found?

442
00:23:39,019 --> 00:23:40,299
It could be the crime scene.

443
00:23:41,138 --> 00:23:44,459
The taxi company said
that the car is almost at its scrap age,

444
00:23:44,939 --> 00:23:46,219
but they haven't dealt with it.

445
00:23:46,219 --> 00:23:47,384
They'll tow it over tomorrow.

446
00:23:48,259 --> 00:23:49,739
Ding Yu is working in this city

447
00:23:49,858 --> 00:23:50,858
as a ride-hailing driver.

448
00:23:51,858 --> 00:23:54,338
We've already found
his address and contact information.

449
00:23:54,818 --> 00:23:56,618
Master is probably almost there now.

450
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,280
What about Han Zhao?

451
00:24:01,858 --> 00:24:03,178
Is she really going abroad?

452
00:24:05,259 --> 00:24:06,178
Maybe.

453
00:24:06,779 --> 00:24:11,098
I saw that post she made on Moments.

454
00:24:11,898 --> 00:24:13,259
The shop has been transferred.

455
00:24:14,138 --> 00:24:15,418
Haven't you been in contact?

456
00:24:17,098 --> 00:24:18,059
We have.

457
00:24:20,059 --> 00:24:22,739
Right now, I'm just focusing on my job

458
00:24:23,618 --> 00:24:24,459
and waiting for her

459
00:24:24,578 --> 00:24:27,459
as a friend.

460
00:25:02,539 --> 00:25:05,699
(And this ring you've been wearing)

461
00:25:06,259 --> 00:25:07,378
is made of plastic.

462
00:25:07,739 --> 00:25:09,098
The paint is badly worn.

463
00:25:09,098 --> 00:25:09,818
I speculate

464
00:25:09,939 --> 00:25:11,818
he gave it to you when you played house

465
00:25:11,818 --> 00:25:12,499
as kids.

466
00:26:46,979 --> 00:26:49,939
This balloon carries the baby

467
00:26:49,939 --> 00:26:52,059
into an unknown world.

468
00:26:52,578 --> 00:26:54,378
With fear and curiosity,

469
00:26:54,699 --> 00:26:57,939
the balloon floats and floats.

470
00:26:58,098 --> 00:27:00,378
The baby runs hard.

471
00:27:00,818 --> 00:27:01,979
He hasn't realized

472
00:27:02,219 --> 00:27:04,699
that he has changed and grown.

473
00:27:09,059 --> 00:27:09,699
Sleepy?

474
00:27:10,578 --> 00:27:11,898
Go to sleep, okay?

475
00:27:14,858 --> 00:27:16,019
Good night, Daddy.

476
00:27:16,499 --> 00:27:17,299
Good night.

477
00:27:21,059 --> 00:27:21,699
Be good.

478
00:28:10,098 --> 00:28:10,699
Hello?

479
00:28:12,618 --> 00:28:13,378
Ding Yu.

480
00:28:13,979 --> 00:28:15,499
We're from CID.

481
00:28:16,178 --> 00:28:17,138
CID officers?

482
00:28:17,898 --> 00:28:19,219
What do you need from me?

483
00:28:20,459 --> 00:28:22,299
You know why we're here for you, right?

484
00:28:23,338 --> 00:28:24,618
We're right downstairs.

485
00:28:31,658 --> 00:28:34,299
My child is home. He just fell asleep.

486
00:28:34,418 --> 00:28:37,019
Whatever it is,
can we wait until tomorrow?

487
00:28:38,178 --> 00:28:39,138
Ding Youcai.

488
00:28:46,019 --> 00:28:46,979
You raise the kid alone?

489
00:28:47,418 --> 00:28:48,378
Please keep it down.

490
00:28:48,939 --> 00:28:50,219
Thank you.

491
00:28:51,658 --> 00:28:52,472
Where's his mother?

492
00:28:54,019 --> 00:28:54,939
We broke up.

493
00:28:57,219 --> 00:28:58,499
You found my dad?

494
00:28:59,578 --> 00:29:00,858
Why there?

495
00:29:01,979 --> 00:29:03,059
It's close to the hometown.

496
00:29:03,699 --> 00:29:05,098
He was superstitious,

497
00:29:05,578 --> 00:29:07,539
always talking about
returning to his roots.

498
00:29:08,578 --> 00:29:10,219
Too bad he didn't rest in a coffin.

499
00:29:11,378 --> 00:29:15,658
Weren't you afraid of being discovered
burning spirit money in the night?

500
00:29:17,299 --> 00:29:18,658
I was scared.

501
00:29:18,658 --> 00:29:20,219
So I didn't dare burn too much.

502
00:29:22,418 --> 00:29:27,578
You moved in with your dad
right after graduating from junior high?

503
00:29:28,178 --> 00:29:29,299
Were you close?

504
00:29:30,858 --> 00:29:31,818
Just so-so.

505
00:29:33,178 --> 00:29:34,578
I heard you often argued.

506
00:29:35,338 --> 00:29:37,699
I was young and simple-minded.

507
00:29:39,178 --> 00:29:40,578
Then why did you kill him?

508
00:29:40,858 --> 00:29:42,219
I-I didn't kill him.

509
00:29:42,618 --> 00:29:43,979
I didn't kill my dad.

510
00:29:46,098 --> 00:29:47,578
We came to see you today

511
00:29:47,578 --> 00:29:49,219
because we have obtained evidence.

512
00:29:50,499 --> 00:29:52,618
I-I'm telling the truth.

513
00:29:53,019 --> 00:29:55,299
I admit, I buried the body.

514
00:29:55,299 --> 00:29:56,459
But I didn't kill him.

515
00:29:56,939 --> 00:29:59,299
When I got that call and rushed over,

516
00:29:59,578 --> 00:30:00,898
he was already dead.

517
00:30:01,378 --> 00:30:02,499
Explain then.

518
00:30:04,779 --> 00:30:05,779
What call?

519
00:30:10,259 --> 00:30:11,059
Not driving today?

520
00:30:11,059 --> 00:30:11,898
I just got back.

521
00:30:39,832 --> 00:30:41,112
(Ding Youcai)

522
00:30:45,272 --> 00:30:47,256
(Cover my shift in South City.)

523
00:32:18,818 --> 00:32:20,299
If you didn't kill him,

524
00:32:20,378 --> 00:32:21,858
why didn't you call the police?

525
00:32:22,539 --> 00:32:24,219
I was afraid
the police would suspect me.

526
00:32:25,178 --> 00:32:27,699
What were you afraid of
if you didn't do anything?

527
00:32:27,818 --> 00:32:30,338
My relationship with my dad
was always pretty tense.

528
00:32:31,378 --> 00:32:33,578
I saw on TV and online

529
00:32:33,779 --> 00:32:35,219
that whenever there's a homicide,

530
00:32:35,578 --> 00:32:37,779
the police always suspect
people close to the victim.

531
00:32:38,539 --> 00:32:39,818
Your relationship was tense?

532
00:32:39,939 --> 00:32:40,499
Why?

533
00:32:41,418 --> 00:32:42,699
He wronged my mom.

534
00:32:43,979 --> 00:32:45,459
Even though we lived together,

535
00:32:46,499 --> 00:32:48,378
I couldn't get over it.

536
00:32:50,578 --> 00:32:53,098
Who called you then?

537
00:32:53,178 --> 00:32:55,699
The call and text
were both from my dad's phone.

538
00:32:56,418 --> 00:32:57,618
The call didn't go through.

539
00:32:58,059 --> 00:33:00,499
The text just told me
to pick him up at that place.

540
00:33:01,378 --> 00:33:03,178
But whether my dad sent it himself,

541
00:33:03,539 --> 00:33:04,499
I don't know.

542
00:33:05,699 --> 00:33:06,459
Then what?

543
00:33:07,378 --> 00:33:09,178
Then I headed towards our hometown.

544
00:33:09,539 --> 00:33:12,299
On the way, I bought
some spirit money and paper ingots.

545
00:33:13,178 --> 00:33:15,418
Where did you buy those late at night?

546
00:33:16,019 --> 00:33:19,939
I-I remember it was
a 24-hour funeral supply shop.

547
00:33:20,259 --> 00:33:21,818
Near a hospital, I think.

548
00:33:24,299 --> 00:33:28,019
What tool did you use to dig the hole?

549
00:33:29,299 --> 00:33:30,299
A shovel.

550
00:33:35,578 --> 00:33:37,939
(It was always in the trunk
of the taxi.)

551
00:33:39,259 --> 00:33:40,920
(Because we often drove to the suburbs.)

552
00:33:41,578 --> 00:33:42,418
(The roads were bad,)

553
00:33:43,338 --> 00:33:44,699
(full of bumps and ditches.)

554
00:33:44,699 --> 00:33:45,784
(The car could get stuck.)

555
00:33:47,499 --> 00:33:49,378
(So we always kept a shovel.)

556
00:35:33,218 --> 00:35:36,539
After that,
I found a place to wash the car,

557
00:35:37,019 --> 00:35:38,178
returned it to the company,

558
00:35:38,778 --> 00:35:41,979
and told them
my dad had gone back to our hometown.

559
00:35:43,738 --> 00:35:45,499
This is the phone
my dad used at the time.

560
00:35:45,539 --> 00:35:46,899
The number was canceled.

561
00:35:47,419 --> 00:35:48,339
But I kept the phone.

562
00:35:48,859 --> 00:35:50,658
I wanted to sell it second-hand.

563
00:35:54,738 --> 00:35:56,298
If I go to jail,

564
00:35:56,618 --> 00:35:57,578
my son...

565
00:35:58,578 --> 00:36:00,459
No other relatives?

566
00:36:01,578 --> 00:36:03,059
There are some on my mom's side,

567
00:36:04,178 --> 00:36:05,979
but we haven't been in touch for years.

568
00:36:07,618 --> 00:36:10,499
Your dad liked Teresa Teng?

569
00:36:13,778 --> 00:36:15,618
That CD is genuine.

570
00:36:16,178 --> 00:36:18,178
The limited edition is hard to get.

571
00:36:22,098 --> 00:36:23,218
My mom liked her.

572
00:36:24,379 --> 00:36:26,098
My dad liked listening to Teresa Teng

573
00:36:26,698 --> 00:36:28,138
under the influence of my mom.

574
00:36:29,178 --> 00:36:32,138
Back then, they got along pretty well.

575
00:36:33,499 --> 00:36:34,979
My dad bought the CD himself.

576
00:36:35,539 --> 00:36:37,218
It was always in his car.

577
00:36:37,218 --> 00:36:38,578
He never even got to open it.

578
00:36:39,512 --> 00:36:41,048
So I thought I'd save it for his trip.

579
00:36:43,059 --> 00:36:44,738
Let's talk about Yu Meigui.

580
00:36:45,298 --> 00:36:46,419
I wasn't close to her.

581
00:36:49,019 --> 00:36:51,419
She left after my dad was gone.

582
00:36:52,578 --> 00:36:53,379
Where did she go?

583
00:36:54,939 --> 00:36:55,819
I don't know.

584
00:36:56,419 --> 00:36:57,618
Probably home?

585
00:37:00,459 --> 00:37:01,859
Did they register their marriage?

586
00:37:02,738 --> 00:37:03,419
No.

587
00:37:03,899 --> 00:37:05,899
She wasn't old enough
when she first came.

588
00:37:06,539 --> 00:37:08,419
But three years ago,
she was in her twenties.

589
00:37:08,419 --> 00:37:09,419
Why not register then?

590
00:37:10,379 --> 00:37:11,819
That's between her and my dad.

591
00:37:12,339 --> 00:37:13,578
How would I know?

592
00:37:14,218 --> 00:37:15,459
How was their relationship?

593
00:37:16,939 --> 00:37:17,899
Just so-so.

594
00:37:18,738 --> 00:37:19,819
You lived together?

595
00:37:20,499 --> 00:37:22,899
Money was tight,
renting one slightly bigger place.

596
00:37:23,459 --> 00:37:24,979
How could we afford two?

597
00:37:27,339 --> 00:37:29,459
So, to your knowledge,

598
00:37:29,859 --> 00:37:33,618
did your dad ever abuse Yu Meigui?

599
00:37:38,819 --> 00:37:42,019
She didn't have
friends or relatives here?

600
00:37:43,658 --> 00:37:45,258
Some hometown fellows, maybe.

601
00:37:45,939 --> 00:37:47,778
There were quite a few people like her.

602
00:37:48,178 --> 00:37:50,218
But I'm not so sure.

603
00:37:50,819 --> 00:37:52,019
Mr. Fang should know.

604
00:37:52,939 --> 00:37:54,459
They seemed pretty close.

605
00:37:56,059 --> 00:37:56,899
Fang Qihang?

606
00:37:57,539 --> 00:37:58,059
Yeah.

607
00:37:58,178 --> 00:38:00,859
They had gatherings
with their fellow people

608
00:38:01,578 --> 00:38:03,218
at Mr. Fang's place.

609
00:38:09,419 --> 00:38:10,658
Dad.

610
00:38:11,939 --> 00:38:13,019
We woke you up, sweetie?

611
00:38:13,819 --> 00:38:14,578
Come here.

612
00:38:16,658 --> 00:38:17,778
Well...

613
00:38:17,778 --> 00:38:20,138
These two uncles are Dad's friends.

614
00:38:20,459 --> 00:38:23,258
We're talking about adult stuff.

615
00:38:23,819 --> 00:38:26,778
You have to go to kindergarten tomorrow.

616
00:38:26,778 --> 00:38:28,778
How about we go inside and sleep?

617
00:38:33,819 --> 00:38:34,379
Be good.

618
00:38:41,698 --> 00:38:43,138
Captain Leng, what do we do now?

619
00:38:43,539 --> 00:38:44,298
What do you think?

620
00:38:46,059 --> 00:38:46,819
Monitor him.

621
00:38:48,098 --> 00:38:51,499
Yu Meigui's passport information,

622
00:38:51,899 --> 00:38:53,138
entry and exit records,

623
00:38:53,658 --> 00:38:55,178
and Fang Qihang's as well,

624
00:38:56,539 --> 00:38:58,339
need to be thoroughly investigated.

625
00:38:59,019 --> 00:38:59,618
Yeah.

626
00:38:59,658 --> 00:39:00,499
Note it down.

627
00:39:00,499 --> 00:39:01,098
Okay.

628
00:39:05,578 --> 00:39:06,298
Captain Leng.

629
00:39:08,258 --> 00:39:12,098
The logistics company
where Ding Yu worked three years ago

630
00:39:12,419 --> 00:39:14,298
confirmed his employment information.

631
00:39:14,499 --> 00:39:15,738
The entry and exit department

632
00:39:15,738 --> 00:39:19,258
didn't find any exit record
of Ruan Shihong, aka Yu Meigui.

633
00:39:19,939 --> 00:39:22,578
Her visa renewal procedures

634
00:39:22,578 --> 00:39:24,979
were handled
by Fang Qihang's travel agency,

635
00:39:25,499 --> 00:39:27,138
even after Ding Youcai's death.

636
00:39:27,979 --> 00:39:30,578
And after Fang Qihang spoke with us,

637
00:39:30,578 --> 00:39:32,408
he booked a flight
heading southwest tomorrow.

638
00:39:35,218 --> 00:39:36,019
He's running away.

639
00:39:40,899 --> 00:39:42,178
- Give my money back.
- I want my money.

640
00:39:42,298 --> 00:39:43,379
- Give my money back.
- Where are you?

641
00:39:43,379 --> 00:39:44,059
- Come out.
- Come out.

642
00:39:44,059 --> 00:39:46,539
- Give my money back.
- Give my money back.

643
00:39:46,539 --> 00:39:47,419
- Where are you?
- Give my money back.

644
00:39:47,419 --> 00:39:48,218
Fang Qihang!

645
00:39:48,339 --> 00:39:48,859
Open up.

646
00:39:49,379 --> 00:39:50,258
What are you doing?

647
00:39:50,258 --> 00:39:50,778
Pay up!

648
00:39:51,379 --> 00:39:52,258
Police!

649
00:39:52,578 --> 00:39:53,859
Police. We are police.

650
00:39:54,539 --> 00:39:55,499
Put that down.

651
00:39:55,499 --> 00:39:56,339
Perfect timing, sir.

652
00:39:56,339 --> 00:39:58,138
Arrest that punk Fang Qihang.

653
00:39:58,138 --> 00:39:59,298
He scammed all our money.

654
00:40:01,339 --> 00:40:02,138
Fang Qihang.

655
00:40:03,939 --> 00:40:05,976
Fang Qihang,
we're from the city police department.

656
00:40:07,218 --> 00:40:08,098
Fang Qihang.

657
00:40:09,298 --> 00:40:11,138
Fang Qihang, you've met Captain Leng.

658
00:40:11,539 --> 00:40:12,539
I can't go out.

659
00:40:13,819 --> 00:40:16,138
Those people want trouble.

660
00:40:17,218 --> 00:40:18,298
They're blackmailing me

661
00:40:18,298 --> 00:40:19,578
and threatening me.

662
00:40:20,258 --> 00:40:22,419
Tell him to come out first.

663
00:40:22,618 --> 00:40:23,539
Talk things through.

664
00:40:23,778 --> 00:40:24,499
Fang Qihang.

665
00:40:24,578 --> 00:40:26,339
No matter what dispute you have,

666
00:40:26,339 --> 00:40:27,899
you can sit down and talk.

667
00:40:30,899 --> 00:40:31,698
Fang Qihang.

668
00:40:36,698 --> 00:40:39,899
They couldn't keep their foreign brides

669
00:40:40,098 --> 00:40:41,859
and came here to make trouble.

670
00:40:42,339 --> 00:40:44,618
They picked those girls themselves.

671
00:40:44,618 --> 00:40:47,258
They arranged the marriages there.

672
00:40:47,298 --> 00:40:48,738
They even slept together.

673
00:40:48,738 --> 00:40:50,658
Now that the girls ran away,
they came to me.

674
00:40:50,738 --> 00:40:52,499
It's not like I told them to run away.

675
00:40:53,059 --> 00:40:55,258
I just organized a tour group
to go there.

676
00:40:55,258 --> 00:40:57,098
It has nothing to do with me.

677
00:40:58,459 --> 00:41:00,899
My son didn't even touch her.

678
00:41:01,339 --> 00:41:03,859
That woman ran away
just two days after arrival.

679
00:41:04,059 --> 00:41:06,738
We saved up half our lives
to buy a wife for our son.

680
00:41:06,939 --> 00:41:07,778
She just vanished.

681
00:41:07,778 --> 00:41:08,778
No grandchild for us now.

682
00:41:08,859 --> 00:41:10,738
It's not just our family.

683
00:41:11,019 --> 00:41:12,218
You're just a swindler

684
00:41:12,258 --> 00:41:12,899
scamming money.

685
00:41:12,899 --> 00:41:14,178
- We're the same!
- Give my money back.

686
00:41:14,178 --> 00:41:15,138
He scammed all of us.

687
00:41:15,138 --> 00:41:18,379
- Give my money back.
- Give my money back.

688
00:41:18,379 --> 00:41:19,059
Put it down.

689
00:41:19,499 --> 00:41:21,298
Put that down.

690
00:41:21,298 --> 00:41:21,859
Put it down.

691
00:41:22,218 --> 00:41:22,979
Put it down.

692
00:41:24,979 --> 00:41:25,859
Notify the station.

693
00:41:26,339 --> 00:41:28,059
Ask for some officers.

694
00:41:28,059 --> 00:41:28,578
Yes, sir.

695
00:42:12,899 --> 00:42:13,899
It's been three years.

696
00:42:14,098 --> 00:42:15,578
This car must have been cleaned.

697
00:42:16,379 --> 00:42:17,459
And it's a taxi.

698
00:42:17,459 --> 00:42:18,979
Countless people have ridden in it.

699
00:42:19,939 --> 00:42:21,258
So we have to be careful.

700
00:42:21,778 --> 00:42:23,379
Even if there's nothing on the surface,

701
00:42:23,899 --> 00:42:27,578
we'll definitely find clues
in the sponge or fabric.

702
00:42:28,578 --> 00:42:29,379
Be careful.

703
00:42:32,728 --> 00:42:36,221
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

704
00:42:40,015 --> 00:42:45,336
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

705
00:42:47,409 --> 00:42:52,263
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

706
00:42:53,069 --> 00:42:56,216
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

707
00:42:56,216 --> 00:42:59,320
♪To shield us from the storm♪

708
00:43:01,976 --> 00:43:07,110
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

709
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:14,712
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

710
00:43:16,472 --> 00:43:20,056
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

711
00:43:21,208 --> 00:43:28,648
♪Converging into your form♪

712
00:43:29,080 --> 00:43:31,758
♪Looking up♪

713
00:43:31,758 --> 00:43:35,297
♪Such dazzling glory♪

714
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:38,840
♪Like hope♪

715
00:43:38,840 --> 00:43:42,773
♪Reaching out its arms♪

716
00:43:43,640 --> 00:43:46,292
♪Cloaked in light♪

717
00:43:46,292 --> 00:43:50,776
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

718
00:43:50,776 --> 00:43:53,592
♪Traversing♪

719
00:43:53,592 --> 00:44:00,103
♪The battlefield of fate♪
